POPULAR singer Jesse King has opened up on his new album entitled ‘The Rebirth Medley.’ After a long hiatus from the music scene, Jesse King opened up on his reason for making a deluxe version of his hit songs. Buga, as the singer is fondly called, noted that the new album which was recently released is a recreation of all his songs to reflect who he is in this space and time.   Victony expresses joy months after returning on stage     I’m Blessed is more than a love song, says J. Jeef     Oga Bello praises Sanwo-Olu as 37 filmmakers get N200m…   He said: “I am constantly in motion, reinventing myself and this you will hear through my music. The Rebirth Medley is a bridge between the old and the new, a potpourri of different sounds well blended like butter and bread.” Continuing, Buga revealed the nature of the new album saying, “It’s jazz, it’s soul, it’s hiplife, it’s highlife, it’s Apala, it’s street. It speaks of culture and traditions. The Rebirth Medley shows the versatility of Buga, so I truly hope you enjoy it.” ‘The Rebirth Medley’ is a nine-track album with songs including ‘Baba all the way’, ‘Buga’, ‘Mummy’, and ‘Jennifer/Bolanle,’ amongst others.